            "creation_date": 1594139755,
            "body": "<p>You can filter and get the first one using <code>.findFirst()<\/code>.<\/p>\n<pre><code>Optional&lt;MyEnum&gt; res = Arrays.stream(MyEnum.values())\n                        .filter(e -&gt; myList.contains(e.getValue()))\n                        .findFirst();\n\nif(res.isPresent()){\n   MyEnum data = res.get(); // matched enum\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 62779933,
            "question_id": 62779821,
            "last_edit_date": 1594140528
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/LbZgJ.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 2168983,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1921477,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1921477/fose",
                "reputation": 739,
                "display_name": "fose"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1594140317,
            "creation_date": 1594140317,
            "body": "<p>You could do it like this:<\/p>\n<pre><code>public static void main(String[] args) {\n    List&lt;String&gt; list = Arrays.asList(&quot;A&quot;, &quot;B&quot;, &quot;Test&quot;, &quot;D&quot;);\n\n    Optional&lt;String&gt; match = list.stream().filter(str -&gt; str.equals(Value.Test.name())).findFirst();\n    if (match.isPresent()) {\n        // do something with the match\n        String str = match.get();\n        System.out.println(str);\n    }\n}\n\nprivate enum Value {\n    Test\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
